Reasoning: The paper discusses a landmark result in dynamical systems and its connection to algorithmic randomness. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Dynamical Systems). The paper also touches upon information theory and randomness, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as the second likely sub-category. The paper also involves logical reasoning and proofs, which could fall under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the computational complexity of the Ornstein isomorphism, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
